If we need x86_64 in GHA, we can have some thing like this in env.ps1:
`$arch = if ($env:BUILD_ARCH -eq "x86_64") { "x64" } else { "arm64" }
`

just a guess, maybe `-requiresAny` is causing problems. try something more explicit (didn't test this code, just showing the idea): 

(also, I suggest checking for "arm64" and fallback to "x64", not vice versa.

```
if ($env:BUILD_ARCH -eq "arm64") {
  $arch = "arm64"
  $installationPath = vswhere.exe -latest -requires Microsoft.VisualStudio.Component.VC.Tools.arm64 -property installationPath
} else {
  $arch = "x64"
  $installationPath = vswhere.exe -latest -requires Microsoft.VisualStudio.Component.VC.Tools.x86.x64 -property installationPath
}
```

